video.title: Eastsiders
video.synopsis: Cal turns to his friends for help through a hilariously dark time when he discovers that his partner Thom's been cheating on him.

episodes.synopsis: Confronted with his infidelity, Thom promises Cal that he'll stop seeing Jeremy. Cal turns to his sharp-tongued best friend Kathy for solace.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: Flashing back to the night before, Cal tries to forget his troubles at a party, but Thom keeps making things worse. The guys meet Kathy's boyfriend.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: Cal's attempt to confront Jeremy about his affair with Thom takes a disastrous turn. Meanwhile, a conversation with Ian puts Kathy's mind at ease.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: Jeremy attempts to disrupt Cal and Thom's relationship, but they're devoted to fixing their problems. Cal gets unwanted attention from his boss.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Jeremy opens up about Thom and Cal in a pot-fueled conversation with his sister, Kathy calls on Cal in an emergency, and Thom confesses to Cal.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: Things get out of hand when Paul and Cal celebrate a success, Quincy lets Kathy's secret slip, and Jeremy tries to patch things up with Thom and Cal.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: As Cal and Thom prepare to move out of their apartment, Jeremy asks Thom to move in with him. Kathy seeks Cal's support after a fight with Ian.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: In a flashback to a year earlier, Cal and Thom have just moved into their apartment, and Kathy shares details of her first date with Ian.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: After reconciling with Cal, Kathy guides him through a difficult farewell. Kathy and Ian talk things out, and Cal and Thom come to a decision.
episodes.title: Episode 9

episodes.synopsis: Thom and Cal's new direction takes them back to Thom's house, but with a new wake-up call. Cal's estranged sister Hillary lands on his doorstep.
episodes.title: Weirder Than Normal

episodes.synopsis: Cal and Thom take Trevor to Douglas and Quincy's Bastille Day party. On her last night in town, Kathy meets up with the guys to say goodbye.
episodes.title: Sodom (and Gommorah)

episodes.synopsis: There's a new state of affairs in Silver Lake as friends demand details from Cal and Thom and Vera takes a slight detour on the way to her wedding.
episodes.title: Sex Therapy

episodes.synopsis: After their bridal shower, Bri reveals she's worried that Vera is cheating. Cal and Thom's visit to the free clinic gets more than uncomfortable.
episodes.title: Thick Like a Lotion

episodes.synopsis: Cal's mother comes into town to attend his new gallery show. Douglas wonders why Quincy downplays their relationship to their co-workers.
episodes.title: Open Bar

episodes.synopsis: Relationships, brunch and a lazy Sunday have different meanings for the friends, especially Cal, who has a big decision to make about his future.
episodes.title: Evolving

episodes.synopsis: Douglas and Quincy struggle with their complicated relationship -- and a broken down convertible -- on their way to a drag gig.
episodes.title: Priscilla

episodes.synopsis: While on a road trip to move from New York City to Silver Lake, Thom and Cal cross paths with a handsome stranger at a gas station.
episodes.title: Goodbye to All That Shit

episodes.synopsis: After a night of passion and suspense in their camper, Cal and Thom wake to find their circumstances have changed.
episodes.title: Thelma and Louise

episodes.synopsis: Ian, sensing that Hillary needs some alone time, starts taking walks around the neighborhood, where he runs into someone from his past.
episodes.title: Cats

episodes.synopsis: Still barreling westward on their road trip, Thom and Cal face some difficult questions about past mistakes and their undetermined future.
episodes.title: Our Own Private Idaho

episodes.synopsis: With that their trip is nearing its end, Thom and Cal make a stop in Portland, where they cross paths with a couple in the hotel bar.
episodes.title: East of Eden

episodes.synopsis: As Hillary drops some big news on Ian, Thom gets mixed messages about his writing from Cliff. Meanwhile, Jeremy and Derrick suffer a scheduling snafu.
episodes.title: A Relationship Like That

episodes.synopsis: Ian gets sidetracked while trying to reconnect with Hillary. Douglas and Quincy struggle with different visions for their big day.
episodes.title: Going Viral

episodes.synopsis: Set a year in the past, Thom crosses paths with Cliff for the first time, Calvin suffers a setback, and Jeremy celebrates an anniversary with Derrick.
episodes.title: Back East

episodes.synopsis: Quincy introduces Douglas to his mother over brunch. Ian talks labels with Lindy. Jeremy and Derrick have a tough conversation.
episodes.title: Pillow Talk

episodes.synopsis: Douglas and Quincy are feeling the ol' nuptial pressure. Meanwhile, Ian ponders his romantic prospects and Derrick and Jeremy get heartbreaking news.
episodes.title: Both Sides Now

episodes.synopsis: The wedding arrives, but Quincy and Douglas aren't the only ones knee-deep in drama. Thom, Cal, Jeremy, Ian, Derrick -- they're all in it, too.
episodes.title: Always Upwards
